  "title": "Bank Network Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Provide technical support for daily IT operations, network maintenance, and infrastructure management.</li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve issues related to IT systems, network performance, and infrastructure in a timely manner.</li><li>Manage and configure user accounts, permissions, and access privileges to maintain system security.</li><li>Monitor and support network operations, applying foundational networking knowledge (e.g., TCP/IP, routing, switching, firewalls, DNS, VPN).</li><li><strong>Take rotation shift duties around the clock to ensure continuous monitoring and smooth operation of IT systems and networks.</strong></li><li>Provide professional input during IT audits and promptly address identified gaps.</li><li>Deliver ad hoc solutions and recommendations as assigned by the Department Head.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirement:</strong></p><ul><li>A passionate individual who is keen to learn and be able to perform professionally. </li><li><strong>Strong Understanding of basic networking concepts and hands-on operational skills.</strong></li><li>Proficient in Mandarin to liaise with internal stakeholders. </li><li>Previous experience working with banks or other financial institutions is preferred.</li><li>Ability to work independently, while also collaborating effectively in a team environment.</li></ul>",
